ween minority literatures in a third national space and proposes a new way of conceptualizing Asian American literature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 0aAmerican fictionxKorean American authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aImperialism in literature. 0aJapanese fictionxKorean authorsxHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / Asian American.2bisacsh  aAsian American.  aColonialism.  aEmpire.  aImperialism.  aJapan.  aKorean American.  aTransnational.  aTranspacific.  aTriangulation.  aZainichi.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073914540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362801440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503628014423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503628014/original  a978-3-11-073914-5  Stanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles